/* Every `image` is REAL aionVIS output: generated by the Synthesis Agent
   (FLUX.2) on the MI300X from that industry's use-case sentence, in a full
   swarm run (labeled by SAM 3, verified by the Critic). Sources live under
   public/industries/; a null image falls back to the placeholder tile.

   The boxes are the images' REAL stored labels (dataset records,
   runs 0015–0025, 2026-07-11), with two transforms applied:
   - display rule: every stored box with conf ≥ 0.35, no per-class cap —
     the tiles show the swarm's full output, not a sample; `chip` marks
     each class's highest-confidence box, which carries the label pill.
     Per-box source confidences are in the comments.
   - coordinates are re-normalized from the square source image to the
     tiles' 4:3 center crop: cy' = (cy − 0.125) / 0.75, h' = h / 0.75. */
type Box = {
  label: string;
  color: string;
  cx: number;
  cy: number;
  w: number;
  h: number;
  chip?: boolean;
};

